# NextGit Project Rules

## Project Overview

NextGit is a Glulx interpreter for the ZX Spectrum Next.

It is based on:
- Git (Glulx interpreter)
- A custom Glk implementation called NextGlk

## Structure

/docs - Documentation
/nextglk - implementation
/tests - tests
/thirdparty - third party code used as references, you don't need to look here unless asked to



## Architecture

Game
  -> Git VM
  -> Glk ABI
  -> NextGlk
  -> Spectrum Next platform

Git must remain as close to upstream as possible.

Do not modify Git VM behaviour unless explicitly requested.

Prefer implementing missing functionality in NextGlk.

## Platform

Target:
- ZX Spectrum Next
- z88dk
- NextZXOS
- SD card storage

Optional:
- Raspberry Pi acceleration

The interpreter must function without the Raspberry Pi.

## Glk

NextGlk is a genuine Glk implementation.

Do not create alternative abstraction layers.

Use:
- glk.h
- gi_dispa.c
- gi_dispa.h

as the ABI contract.

## Memory

Do not implement memory banking inside NextGlk.

Memory banking belongs to:
- VM memory manager
- Story memory subsystem

NextGlk owns:
- UI state
- Image cache
- Platform I/O

## Graphics

Games use:
- Inform 7
- Glulx
- Inline images

Current requirements:
- Inline image display
- No sound

Initial UI layout:

+----------------------+
|       IMAGE          |
+----------------------+
|      TEXT            |
|      TEXT            |
| >                    |
+----------------------+

## Coding Rules

Always provide:
- complete files
- complete functions

Never provide:
- partial snippets
- search-and-replace instructions
- "insert here" guidance

When generating code:
- compileable first
- functional later

Stub implementations are acceptable if clearly marked.

## Development Strategy

1. Match Glk ABI.
2. Build compileable stubs.
3. Replace stubs incrementally.
4. Keep commits small.
5. Prefer understanding over implementation.

## Documentation

Before implementing a subsystem:
- identify ABI
- identify ownership
- document architecture

Prefer documentation before code.

## Current Status

- Git VM integrated
- Glk dispatcher imported
- NextGlk established
- Image subsystem stubbed
- Investigating core Glk object types:
  - winid_t
  - strid_t
  - frefid_t

## Unicode Policy

The Spectrum Next renderer is ASCII-only.

NextGlk must expose the Unicode Glk APIs required by the ABI.

Unicode support is implemented as:

- Accept Unicode input values.
- Internally store Unicode code points where required by Glk.
- Render only ASCII characters directly.
- Non-ASCII characters are replaced by '?' initially.

Allowed implementation:

    U+0000–U+007F  -> render normally
    U+0080+        -> '?'

The Unicode APIs must exist and compile.

Full Unicode rendering is explicitly out of scope for the initial implementation.

Do not remove Unicode APIs from the Glk ABI.
Do not change glk.h.
Do not remove GLK_MODULE_UNICODE.
Prefer stub implementations over API removal.

## Inform 7 Content Policy

Target games are expected to be ASCII-compatible.

Before implementing full Unicode support:

- Verify the target game content.
- Verify generated Inform 7 output.
- Verify Blorb metadata.

If the target game is ASCII-only:

- Unicode APIs remain implemented.
- Unicode rendering remains simplified.
- Non-ASCII output may be replaced with '?'.

Do not implement full Unicode rendering unless a real game requirement is identified.